Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` = lost focus (maps to `Deactivated`); `OnStop` = fully backgrounded (maps to `Stopped`)
- iOS `DidEnterBackground` = fully backgrounded (maps to `Stopped`)
- Keep handlers fast (<5s on Android, limited time on iOS) to avoid ANR/watchdog kills

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback objects, override `OnStopped` on a `Window` subclass — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
protected override void OnStopped()
{
    base.OnStopped();
    Preferences.Set("draft", _vm.Draft);
}
```
